        "UIName": "River Hawk RH-A-SP",
        "Id": "mechdef_riverhawk_RH-A-SP",
        "Name": "River Hawk",
        "Details": "The River Hawk is arguably the greatest failure ever produced by the RAD Group, being originally built for the Star League in 2739 shortly after the Osprey was created, with many referring to it as a '100 ton Charger' thanks to the standard RH-A-SL's massive RADTech 400 standard fusion engine. This, in combination with it's underwhelming weapons setup and a pathetic 10.5 tons of standard armor quickly led to the mech suffering the same fate as the Charger it is often likened to during the Star League era. Like the Charger, it would be saved as a desperate and shattered RAD Group found the production line for the chassis was one of the few left functioning and would manage to sell these machines to the Great Houses during the Succession Wars despite it's flaws, meaning the chassis can be found semi-frequently throughout the Inner Sphere. The RH-A-SP is a model that was quietly released in 3040 for the RAD Group's Site Protection Teams, and would later equally quietly be added to the RAD Group's catalogue for purchase, and is essentially the RH-C-SL with a few cues from the RH-B-SL, being primarily similar to the former, but losing the Endo-Steel chassis due to the RAD Group's orbital facilities being offline at the time the pattern entered production, gaining thicker Ferro-Fibrous armor to make up for it, making it actually more robust than the mech it was based on. The consequence of this lack of Endo-Steel means the RAD Group's in house Polarity GR-M1A1 Gauss Rifle no longer fitted on the mech, being instead replaced by an LBX-10 with slug and cluster munitions, along with CASE to save the chassis should an ammo explosion occur. The ER Large Laser and Small Pulse Laser carried over from the RH-C-SL have also had Laser Insulators applied to them, with the RAD Group retaining the knowledge of their design and putting them back into production. This allows for the removal of two double heat sinks without too much of a loss in cooling.\n\n <b><color=#e51717>N0MERCY and Pappystein Sub-mod</color></b>",
        "Icon": "uixTxrIcon_osprey"
    },
